reviews_data.review_text: Love their milk foam!
Best Boba in Charlotte hands down!

First time at Gong Cha as I was driving on my roadtrip and I was in for a treat! The Taro tea Latte was nice and refreshing in this heat and I also got the Crème Brûlée Croffle! The texture was nice and crispy and the brûlée reminded me of a flan🥰I will definitely be back to try the bubble waffle next time
Favorite place for boba

Just moved into the area , thankfully they had a location here.
They are kinda hidden though
Order comes out so fast good workers
This place was cute and smelled good, but the service was nonexistent. The staff told us to use the iPad checkout because the place was empty, but it wasn’t user-friendly.
Our family's fave spot! My girls are always asking for it. Cream brûlée milk tea's her jam. I stick with Earl Grey milk tea and crystal boba 😋
I hate how the same drink I order tastes different every single time. Not a single worker is consistent for more than a week.
They are OPEN with new menu items! I ordered the mango green tea and it was refreshing as always☺️I love hanging out here and the staff were so helpful too❤️All the snack options look delicious

I tried the new crème brûlée croffle with pearls and it was soooo delicious!!! My barista Alina was truly amazing and so kind. If I could give 6 stars I would this is such wonderful establishment from the people to the cutesy vibes of the store.
It’s open again (5/2/2025)
Google showed open, however seems like this place is closed until further notice. I wonder why the owners could not update Google to reflect that they are closed.
I stopped by this afternoon but the store was closed. Anyone knows if it is closed forever or just temporarily? Hope its not as I love this place
Love this spot! Nice selection and great location.

I can always count on this place to have excellent boba. The Earl Grey Milk Tea and the Wintermelon Milk Tea are my two favorites! I do love milk tea especially, and I do wish if there were more flavors of them here, but I still love coming here regardless. The employees are really nice and willing to give recommendations. Another plus side is that this is one of the cutest boba places ever! I love how the inside is decorated and it is always very clean.

Bobba texture is on point, which is important. I bounce between their milk foams specialty, wintermelon w/ basil & 3JS. I love sweet tea but it’s always much better with some milk and chewy jelly in it. 😉
Been to this location for the first time, I ordered a drink with Aloe topping but when I checked, there's none in the drink and the milk tea tasted watery.
沒有台灣的味道，真失望😔
The baristas were incredibly sweet, and the interior is great, but the bubble tea was very mediocre. I was not impressed. I got a fruit tea, maybe the milk teas are better..
Love their drinks. Used to love their waffle too but they don’t make it anymore

Heads up to FFXIV friends: they still have codes (for now) - the code is only for the King Porxie mount. They only have the fat cat cups and are completely out of the keychains. The requirement is that you need to only buy one of the FFXIV drinks, then you can buy whatever for the other two. Yes, only one code per three drinks.
THE CREME BRULEE STRAWBERRY LATTE  is the best drink and my go to every time I go to gong cha. PLEASE consider trying it.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Strawberry, Pearl, Fresh Milk with Pearl

reviews_data.review_text: It's too scary, there's a hair inside the cup, it makes me want to vomit!
Really good spot if you’re looking to have your boba tea made a certain way. Great to have options on how much sugar and ice goes into your drink.
Best location ever. Love the honey green tea! Love u goncha

I love the boba teas here BUT there’s 2 things that make me rate it a 4 star. One is they can take forever to prepare your order. I think they’re understaffed. The other is they open WAY too late so they miss out on a lot of business.
Very nice, love the place
Nice spot!
Very exquisite!! Outstanding Asian Boba Tea Drink Experience... Highly recommended to try in the future!! 👌🔥
Always nice and the drinks are great! The atmosphere is chill. Love this place!
Got a regular taro slush it was so bland no flavor or sweetness. Literally blended ice and boba. It was $8+ too I’m pissed
The staff is very friendly and my drink was amazing!
fancy interior and good taste
Delicious!  Love the taro boba!
My daughter loves this place so we go a lot. It IS tasty, so it taking her gives me an excuse to get one for myself too 🤓

We stopped in here while in Charlotte for the day. Clean store with trendy decor. The staff was friendly and mixed the drinks well. Strong taste of coffee in the Coffee Milk Tea. Didn’t taste like creamer like other boba shops. They do a seal top here as it mixes. One of the better boba I have had in my travels.
Tea is pretty good. The inside is super cute and colorful and the staff was friendly. The menu is a bit confusing at first. I got a peach green tea and my partner got a brown sugar milk tea.

i came here on a not so busy day and there were only two other girls in the shop, ive read some of the other reviews after getting my drink and i honestly have no idea what some of them are talking about. from what i saw there was only one girl working and she seemed nice enough, our interaction lasted only like a minute.

im not a huge fan of tea to begin with so I usually get juice if the place offers it but i gotta say the strawberry milk tea that i got was pretty good. i could barely taste the tea. ill definitely come back with friends.

I had the pleasure of trying the mango yogurt drink at Gong Cha's Rea Road location, and it was truly exceptional, just like the one at their Kings Drive location. They have successfully maintained the consistency in terms of taste, texture, color, and sweetness. It's an ideal beverage for the summer, offering a delightful combination of sweetness, tartness, and refreshing coldness. The addition of chewy mango pearls adds an extra layer of deliciousness. The interior of the shop has a cool neon vibe perfect for hanging out with friends and family.I highly recommend trying this drink before the summer comes to an end. It's a definite winner! 👍☀️💯
Ordered a milk drink and it was 90% ice, took less than 5 sips to finish. Don’t waste your money here

First of all for everyone the prices on the “menu pictures” are not up to date i paid almost 10$ for only one large drink with two toppings. Not to mention that I got a wrong drink, I ordered a mango yogurt and got a mango green tea even though the cup clearly said yogurt. The staff was really unmotivated, I worked in a boba store for 2 years and can understand that it can be boring or stressful but don’t let it out on the customers. The tea was fine but I probably won’t come back.

Idk why but this is the third time we’ve been out of a handful of times where they’ve ran out of boba. Mind you we got there at 8:08pm. Why even put you’re open until 9 if it’s repetitive? Can’t wait for Milk Cha Cha to open up at Rea Fames cause even 15 mins until close they still don’t run out of boba. This Gong Cha is a joke.

Their quality has gone down real bad. I prefer Milk Cha Cha or Kung fu tea. I asked nicely to that Asian girl who served our tea about strawberry flavor and she has real bad attitude. Not worth paying $6.

They made me wrong order for strawberry yogurt into what it tastes like artificial syrup water. I asked them nicely to make changes to the drink and the Asian girl gives me attitude of not wanting to fix the drink. And they said this is what a yogurt drink taste like !!! I had to persistently ask them to fix the drink and all they said is we will add more water to your drink . What kind of SERVICE AND ATTITUDE IS THIS ????? DONT RECOMMEND ANYONE TO THIS PLACE . SERVICE IS HORRIBLE AND TASTES TERRIBLE
Not a big fan of Gong cha because there’s not once I taste the tea in their tea…looking at it’s high ratings and I think I’m the weird one 💯
Eh. It’s boba. Better than kung fu tea by far. I love the kpop though. This is basically boba for white people who take cute Instagram photos and enjoy BTS’s English songs.
Great atmosphere, really liked the choice of music and the decor. Was disappointed however after trying out their taro milk tea. It tasted as if dirty water was used when making it.

The best boba shop in Charlotte.   I’ve been to a few, but this one is my favorite by far.   The facility is clean and the building has a relaxing atmosphere to enjoy.   I’ve never had a problem with my order and it’s always delicious.   Super fast and friendly service.
Bad experience

Worst experience. We traveled 20 mins for Gong cha and they didn’t have Boba’s at the store. Although, We took sometime to decide our order they didn’t mention it when we entered the store. Really disappointing experience.
Our favorite boba tea place

Gong Cha’s drinks are probably the best in the area. Each time I go I order a new drink and they have never failed to make me happy. The service is quick and friendly and the place’s aesthetic is very cute. 100% recommend! (Try the winter melon milk drink for something sweet ^^)
Dear Gong Cha, we are really happy to have you in our neighborhood , could you please fix your waffle maker🤗😁,yummy drinks.you must try the bubble waffles!

As I walked in, my ears are soothed with a symphony of K-pop tunes, the clatter of the baristas hard at work, and a pleasant ambiance of conversations all around. Look around, and you'll find cute decor and neon signs which create a very fitting mood for this establishment. As I took the first sip, the balls entering my mouth were jarring.... yet pleasantly surprising. And the taste goes without saying.
This establishment has appealed to all 5 of my senses, so I'm giving 1 star for each. I will be returning soon. Very Nice!

Gong cha is my favorite boba shop to visit with my friends. It is the perfect place to hang out and they even have kpop playing on the TV. The staff are very friendly and helped me picked a drink that I later loved. The service was quick and efficient and I will definitely come back to visit.
Excellent customer service and fast drinks. Sometimes out of one or two ingredients/toppings, but its no problem when theres dozens of other menu items to choose from! Will be returning!
boba? sounds like booba. i like this place
It's nice to see good, young workers at an establishment such as this. Although some menu items seem out of stock very often, the drinks that are offered are still great.
I love this place I love to poop in the restroom and not flush
I always love coming here after school and getting drinks for me and my mom. I also come here because the workers are nice and understand when I am confused about what to order. I appreciate it here!

All viewers: please do yourself a favor and do not bother getting bubble tea here. This establishment lacks leadership and managements presence. The shop is left to be run by underage children who lack customer service. The children working are disrespectful, unprofessional, and lazy. An owners nightmare. I encourage the owner of this location to take better pride in his business and either train the children he’s hiring or hire individuals who care about what they are doing. The children at this location turn away business customer after customer not only because of their attitudes but mainly because they are lazy. They constantly tell you that they are out of a product or flavor because they do not want to make the drinks. The location is closed early all the time as well. Again any owners nightmare. Do yourself a favor and visit another bubble tea shop to avoid pour treatment by teens. I would love to give this location zero stars.

amazing!
boba aside, the workers are great. i was helped by the most handsome and fine man i have ever seen. the only downside about this place is i wasnt able to focus on my work because i kept getting distracted by the hot worker. hire more ppl like him everytime he opened his mouth i couldnt do anythingbut foam at the mouth. the drink was okay too.
Ambience was super but not a place for Boba :(

I have gone several times since I do like the Brown sugar tea. I brought one home for a family member and both he and I had bad stomachs for the rest of the day. I felt even though I asked for half sugar it seemed very sweet from the last time I went. Not sure if it was the milk . I do think the place has good atmosphere for teens and has a nice variety, but giving the benefit of the doubt on stars... I think it was my last time.
I love this place! Everyone is friendly, it’s beautifully decorated, and the boba tea is so good! My go to is the coffee milk tea (black tea) with boba in it, I love it!!

This was my first time there and I was not impressed. Ordered the taro milk tea less ice half sugar and mango smoothie regular sugar. The taro milk tea had an odd flavor. Almost like dirty water. Not sure how to explain it but def could not drink it. The bubbles had a nice consistency and flavor unfortunately didn’t get to enjoy them. The mango smoothie had absolutely no flavor. I noticed that they added three cups of ice when making it and then proceeded to add some water while it was blending to smooth it out. I didn’t think much of that but it def impacted the flavor. The environment is cute spot for teens. It was pretty busy when I went in, I ordered as soon as I got in but waited about 20 minutes for both drinks. I won’t be back.
Nice place for a summer drink, which is different from the usual.
Not the  great milk teas you will find here. All milk teas here are made with milk powder and you can literally feel powder in your milk tea.
Good boba!
It was sooooo good I've been many times you have to try different things till you get the right one but once you find it it's amazing
Great place for some boba, they have many flavor options, they don't have popping boba though which was a bummer but other than that it's a great cute place to hang out

I love coming here, I never have a problem with the staff because they are usually very nice. But the encounter with this girl makes me not want to return, she was extremely rude to the point where it caught me off guard. Did not leave a tip. I really love the boba tea here but this lady left me in tears .

My 13yo and I come here at least once a week to enjoy boba tea. Soooo good! Only once did we get the wrong thing, but it ended up still being good! Always excellent customer service as well. So happy to have an excellent boba place in the south Charlotte area.
Friendly, fast service.

We first drank this in NJ(once a week for the whole summer). I was so excited to find this place in Charlotte. Awesome feeling to have this.

Edit: the more I visit, the more it is getting worse. Taste isn't good as it used to be. Options/customizations are less.

Edit: out if my past 15+ visits, the common denominator of all my bad drinks is the lady behind the counter with most pins and white/translucent glasses. She messes up my drinks. They won't taste good at all.
Today she messed up two drinks, I'm not sure why she is frustrated on my and messed them up again.

After paying freaking $16 for two drinks Everytime, I don't expect this service.
Great place for some quality drinks. Staff was quick, efficient, and respectful. It's easy to order off the menu and there are a plethora of choices to choose from! Highly recommend.
I had the crème brûlée strawberry with nothing added and I think that was the best drink I've ever had. Definitely coming again sometime soon!
I like this place , the best boba tea in Charlotte.
This boba is god-like
Ordered some BUBBLE teas the other day, and I'll say they forgot to put enough milk powders in it. NO MILK TASTE AT ALL!!!!!
Good bubble tea, but need to have milk alternatives for those who are lactose intolerant. Would be nice to have almond or soy substitute for us

This place is too busy with online orders to focus on customers right in front of them. The workers are working to hard and get too mixed up. We came here for Waffle and ice cream but they said it would take too long. Always seems too have some sorta of problem. The smoothies and teas are ok but much better selection and flavor at other places. I will never be going to any gong cha always a headache and some problems at every location I’ve been too.
went yesterday, messed up my order after waiting 15 minutes with 2 people working but god bless those kids behind the counter.  really should hire 1-2 more people during those rush hour crowds.

Went with all my kids and we were all delighted with our bobba tea!!!  It was our first time here and the staff was very patient explaining the options and recommending flavors to try. We are definitely making this a weekly tradition. Highly recommend! 😁😁
And they're very COVID safe, so that's another plus!!

Order three fresh milk tea with pearl in Stone Crest, not sure if the milk goes bad or any ingredient in it goes bad, taste sour. And the milk tea taste watery, not enough tea flavor.  Prefer the gong cha in Kings Dr., they make bubble milk tea milk better.
Awesome place..
Order for my friend… he liked it
I've been here 30 minutes and still haven't got my 2 drinks. They have 3 workers and there's not even 15 customers at one time. Terribly slow service.
They know how to make really good teas def visit! My gf loved this place
Worker is crazy about mask wearing, regardless of no mandate and vaccines and being like 15 feet away
I love this place it is very comfortable and the drinks are really good. I recommend.😁👍👍
Great place! It is very covid friendly and has a great selection of drinks. The staff was very friendly and I had a great time + a great drink!
this was such good boba!! i love it so much, got purple sweet potato smoothie and i really recommend it!!
very homey and comfortable place to stop by! great staff and i love how they still required masks as they are a local business. great service and drinks :)))
Staff is rude.  Went in fully vaccinated after CDC mandate to wear masks had been lifted and the girl behind the counter demanded I put one on.  She was insulting, condescending and rude.
First time trying and I'm impressed! Long line but still fast service. Wish masubi was an option 🤤
They are very slow and showed no patience. Be prepared for 25min for only a drink!

So cuteee!! This is my favorite Boba place in Charlotte rn, I'm so glad my friend invited me because I had no clue it was there!! All the drinks I've tried have been good but my favorites are the brown sugar teas :)
Great selections

Tons of options and combinations to choose from. You can totally make a customized concoction or select one from the menu. We got a Brown Sugar Milk Tea with black tea, less ice (70%, but wish we'd done 100%), less sugar (70%, but wish we'd done just 50% on this one), and added black pearl for extra $0.75. We also got an Earl Grey Milk Tea with 3Js with less ice (70%), half sugar (50%), and the 3Js (black pearl, grass, pudding). I did not care for the grass or pudding though, so I would say just black pearls next time.

There's a lot to choose from so we'd definitely go back if we were in the area and looking for some afternoon refreshments.
Best bubble tea in Charlotte!!!
Great taro smoothie and passion fruit green tea.

I lived in Korea for 2 years and one of my favorite chains was Gong Cha. Feeling nostalgic for my home away from home I stopped in one day when I happened to drive past this one. I tasted my drink and nearly cried. It is exactly like Korea and so so good. Please support these folks. They are kind and make the best drinks.

I had a boba milk tea with red bean. It was great. A lot of black pearl(boba). My first time. Didn’t realize they have taro, will try that too next time.
It took them a while to make it. Not sure what was the issue. Everyone came after me got their drinks, I became impatient, but it ends well. Probably should say something if it takes a bit longer ... I loved it.
Delicious! Very clean place with friendly service. Try the waffles!

The bubble tea is sooo good. The tea isn’t that strong and the bubbles ar really chewy. The menu is huge and gives you so many options to choose from and to customize your drink. The price is a little bit on the expensive side but it is totally worth it. I am definitely going again.

Not sure what it was but maybe the way drinks are made here tastes a bit more flavorful than their midtown location? My cousin recommended coming here since she went on soft opening and got their strawberry creme brulee latte. She raved about how delicious it was, so I bought one for my wife as she loves strawberry drinks. I had tried it too, we both agreed that it was good. So my wife made me go back to buy 3 more! Earl grey 3js is pretty good. Taro tastes powdery but beats the one in midtown as it tastes watery there. Which I don’t even know why. Will be back since we live close by!

I ordered a Taro milk tea, and it tasted like water with a bit of Taro. I’ve had this tea in other Boba Tea places and it’s doesn’t taste like that at all. Very disappointed. I complained about the flavor and they didn’t offer me any solutions rather that telling me that “is just how our tea taste”. I guess then their tea just taste bad then. I would not recommend them at all. So disappointed! People told me not to come to this place and I guess they were right.
The best bubble tea in town🧋🤍
Love this place. There’s a finally a boba place that’s close to me and the inside is decorated so cute!! The menu is great!! Lovely people as well!

Very excited that Gong Cha opened their second location especially in Stonecrest! The menu is the same as their metropolitan location, but still good! The building inside is really nice. Friendly staff and nice decor. Definitely recommend visiting their new location!

I’m thrilled that Gongcha has opened their second location here in Charlotte. The one in Midtown is my go to spot because it’s near my house and I used to go to CPCC. I tried this place because they offered 50% off all drinks for the grand opening.

My favorite drinks so far are strawberry milk foam green tea and passion fruit green tea.

The decorations are modern and stylish at first glance. It’s hard to tell if it’s spacious now because they haven’t put their tables out due to the pandemic.

I hope to see their full decorations after the pandemic is over.

Worst experience. We traveled 20 mins for Gong cha and they didn’t have Boba’s at the store. Although, We took sometime to decide our order they didn’t mention it when we entered the store. Really disappointing experience.
Our favorite boba tea place

Gong Cha’s drinks are probably the best in the area. Each time I go I order a new drink and they have never failed to make me happy. The service is quick and friendly and the place’s aesthetic is very cute. 100% recommend! (Try the winter melon milk drink for something sweet ^^)
Dear Gong Cha, we are really happy to have you in our neighborhood , could you please fix your waffle maker🤗😁,yummy drinks.you must try the bubble waffles!

As I walked in, my ears are soothed with a symphony of K-pop tunes, the clatter of the baristas hard at work, and a pleasant ambiance of conversations all around. Look around, and you'll find cute decor and neon signs which create a very fitting mood for this establishment. As I took the first sip, the balls entering my mouth were jarring.... yet pleasantly surprising. And the taste goes without saying.
This establishment has appealed to all 5 of my senses, so I'm giving 1 star for each. I will be returning soon. Very Nice!

Gong cha is my favorite boba shop to visit with my friends. It is the perfect place to hang out and they even have kpop playing on the TV. The staff are very friendly and helped me picked a drink that I later loved. The service was quick and efficient and I will definitely come back to visit.
Excellent customer service and fast drinks. Sometimes out of one or two ingredients/toppings, but its no problem when theres dozens of other menu items to choose from! Will be returning!
boba? sounds like booba. i like this place
It's nice to see good, young workers at an establishment such as this. Although some menu items seem out of stock very often, the drinks that are offered are still great.
I love this place I love to poop in the restroom and not flush
I always love coming here after school and getting drinks for me and my mom. I also come here because the workers are nice and understand when I am confused about what to order. I appreciate it here!

All viewers: please do yourself a favor and do not bother getting bubble tea here. This establishment lacks leadership and managements presence. The shop is left to be run by underage children who lack customer service. The children working are disrespectful, unprofessional, and lazy. An owners nightmare. I encourage the owner of this location to take better pride in his business and either train the children he’s hiring or hire individuals who care about what they are doing. The children at this location turn away business customer after customer not only because of their attitudes but mainly because they are lazy. They constantly tell you that they are out of a product or flavor because they do not want to make the drinks. The location is closed early all the time as well. Again any owners nightmare. Do yourself a favor and visit another bubble tea shop to avoid pour treatment by teens. I would love to give this location zero stars.

amazing!
boba aside, the workers are great. i was helped by the most handsome and fine man i have ever seen. the only downside about this place is i wasnt able to focus on my work because i kept getting distracted by the hot worker. hire more ppl like him everytime he opened his mouth i couldnt do anythingbut foam at the mouth. the drink was okay too.
Ambience was super but not a place for Boba :(

I have gone several times since I do like the Brown sugar tea. I brought one home for a family member and both he and I had bad stomachs for the rest of the day. I felt even though I asked for half sugar it seemed very sweet from the last time I went. Not sure if it was the milk . I do think the place has good atmosphere for teens and has a nice variety, but giving the benefit of the doubt on stars... I think it was my last time.
I love this place! Everyone is friendly, it’s beautifully decorated, and the boba tea is so good! My go to is the coffee milk tea (black tea) with boba in it, I love it!!

This was my first time there and I was not impressed. Ordered the taro milk tea less ice half sugar and mango smoothie regular sugar. The taro milk tea had an odd flavor. Almost like dirty water. Not sure how to explain it but def could not drink it. The bubbles had a nice consistency and flavor unfortunately didn’t get to enjoy them. The mango smoothie had absolutely no flavor. I noticed that they added three cups of ice when making it and then proceeded to add some water while it was blending to smooth it out. I didn’t think much of that but it def impacted the flavor. The environment is cute spot for teens. It was pretty busy when I went in, I ordered as soon as I got in but waited about 20 minutes for both drinks. I won’t be back.
Nice place for a summer drink, which is different from the usual.
Not the  great milk teas you will find here. All milk teas here are made with milk powder and you can literally feel powder in your milk tea.
Good boba!
It was sooooo good I've been many times you have to try different things till you get the right one but once you find it it's amazing
Great place for some boba, they have many flavor options, they don't have popping boba though which was a bummer but other than that it's a great cute place to hang out

I love coming here, I never have a problem with the staff because they are usually very nice. But the encounter with this girl makes me not want to return, she was extremely rude to the point where it caught me off guard. Did not leave a tip. I really love the boba tea here but this lady left me in tears .

My 13yo and I come here at least once a week to enjoy boba tea. Soooo good! Only once did we get the wrong thing, but it ended up still being good! Always excellent customer service as well. So happy to have an excellent boba place in the south Charlotte area.
Friendly, fast service.

We first drank this in NJ(once a week for the whole summer). I was so excited to find this place in Charlotte. Awesome feeling to have this.

Edit: the more I visit, the more it is getting worse. Taste isn't good as it used to be. Options/customizations are less.

Edit: out if my past 15+ visits, the common denominator of all my bad drinks is the lady behind the counter with most pins and white/translucent glasses. She messes up my drinks. They won't taste good at all.
Today she messed up two drinks, I'm not sure why she is frustrated on my and messed them up again.

After paying freaking $16 for two drinks Everytime, I don't expect this service.
Great place for some quality drinks. Staff was quick, efficient, and respectful. It's easy to order off the menu and there are a plethora of choices to choose from! Highly recommend.
I had the crème brûlée strawberry with nothing added and I think that was the best drink I've ever had. Definitely coming again sometime soon!
I like this place , the best boba tea in Charlotte.
This boba is god-like
Ordered some BUBBLE teas the other day, and I'll say they forgot to put enough milk powders in it. NO MILK TASTE AT ALL!!!!!
Good bubble tea, but need to have milk alternatives for those who are lactose intolerant. Would be nice to have almond or soy substitute for us

This place is too busy with online orders to focus on customers right in front of them. The workers are working to hard and get too mixed up. We came here for Waffle and ice cream but they said it would take too long. Always seems too have some sorta of problem. The smoothies and teas are ok but much better selection and flavor at other places. I will never be going to any gong cha always a headache and some problems at every location I’ve been too.
went yesterday, messed up my order after waiting 15 minutes with 2 people working but god bless those kids behind the counter.  really should hire 1-2 more people during those rush hour crowds.

Went with all my kids and we were all delighted with our bobba tea!!!  It was our first time here and the staff was very patient explaining the options and recommending flavors to try. We are definitely making this a weekly tradition. Highly recommend! 😁😁
And they're very COVID safe, so that's another plus!!

Order three fresh milk tea with pearl in Stone Crest, not sure if the milk goes bad or any ingredient in it goes bad, taste sour. And the milk tea taste watery, not enough tea flavor.  Prefer the gong cha in Kings Dr., they make bubble milk tea milk better.
Awesome place..
Order for my friend… he liked it
I've been here 30 minutes and still haven't got my 2 drinks. They have 3 workers and there's not even 15 customers at one time. Terribly slow service.
They know how to make really good teas def visit! My gf loved this place
Worker is crazy about mask wearing, regardless of no mandate and vaccines and being like 15 feet away
I love this place it is very comfortable and the drinks are really good. I recommend.😁👍👍
Great place! It is very covid friendly and has a great selection of drinks. The staff was very friendly and I had a great time + a great drink!
this was such good boba!! i love it so much, got purple sweet potato smoothie and i really recommend it!!
very homey and comfortable place to stop by! great staff and i love how they still required masks as they are a local business. great service and drinks :)))
Staff is rude.  Went in fully vaccinated after CDC mandate to wear masks had been lifted and the girl behind the counter demanded I put one on.  She was insulting, condescending and rude.
First time trying and I'm impressed! Long line but still fast service. Wish masubi was an option 🤤
They are very slow and showed no patience. Be prepared for 25min for only a drink!

So cuteee!! This is my favorite Boba place in Charlotte rn, I'm so glad my friend invited me because I had no clue it was there!! All the drinks I've tried have been good but my favorites are the brown sugar teas :)
Great selections

Tons of options and combinations to choose from. You can totally make a customized concoction or select one from the menu. We got a Brown Sugar Milk Tea with black tea, less ice (70%, but wish we'd done 100%), less sugar (70%, but wish we'd done just 50% on this one), and added black pearl for extra $0.75. We also got an Earl Grey Milk Tea with 3Js with less ice (70%), half sugar (50%), and the 3Js (black pearl, grass, pudding). I did not care for the grass or pudding though, so I would say just black pearls next time.

There's a lot to choose from so we'd definitely go back if we were in the area and looking for some afternoon refreshments.
Best bubble tea in Charlotte!!!
Great taro smoothie and passion fruit green tea.

I lived in Korea for 2 years and one of my favorite chains was Gong Cha. Feeling nostalgic for my home away from home I stopped in one day when I happened to drive past this one. I tasted my drink and nearly cried. It is exactly like Korea and so so good. Please support these folks. They are kind and make the best drinks.

I had a boba milk tea with red bean. It was great. A lot of black pearl(boba). My first time. Didn’t realize they have taro, will try that too next time.
It took them a while to make it. Not sure what was the issue. Everyone came after me got their drinks, I became impatient, but it ends well. Probably should say something if it takes a bit longer ... I loved it.
Delicious! Very clean place with friendly service. Try the waffles!

The bubble tea is sooo good. The tea isn’t that strong and the bubbles ar really chewy. The menu is huge and gives you so many options to choose from and to customize your drink. The price is a little bit on the expensive side but it is totally worth it. I am definitely going again.

Not sure what it was but maybe the way drinks are made here tastes a bit more flavorful than their midtown location? My cousin recommended coming here since she went on soft opening and got their strawberry creme brulee latte. She raved about how delicious it was, so I bought one for my wife as she loves strawberry drinks. I had tried it too, we both agreed that it was good. So my wife made me go back to buy 3 more! Earl grey 3js is pretty good. Taro tastes powdery but beats the one in midtown as it tastes watery there. Which I don’t even know why. Will be back since we live close by!

I ordered a Taro milk tea, and it tasted like water with a bit of Taro. I’ve had this tea in other Boba Tea places and it’s doesn’t taste like that at all. Very disappointed. I complained about the flavor and they didn’t offer me any solutions rather that telling me that “is just how our tea taste”. I guess then their tea just taste bad then. I would not recommend them at all. So disappointed! People told me not to come to this place and I guess they were right.
The best bubble tea in town🧋🤍
Love this place. There’s a finally a boba place that’s close to me and the inside is decorated so cute!! The menu is great!! Lovely people as well!

Very excited that Gong Cha opened their second location especially in Stonecrest! The menu is the same as their metropolitan location, but still good! The building inside is really nice. Friendly staff and nice decor. Definitely recommend visiting their new location!

I’m thrilled that Gongcha has opened their second location here in Charlotte. The one in Midtown is my go to spot because it’s near my house and I used to go to CPCC. I tried this place because they offered 50% off all drinks for the grand opening.

My favorite drinks so far are strawberry milk foam green tea and passion fruit green tea.

The decorations are modern and stylish at first glance. It’s hard to tell if it’s spacious now because they haven’t put their tables out due to the pandemic.

I hope to see their full decorations after the pandemic is over.
